    He is an author of over 500 publications in International Refereed Scientific Journals, over 33 Refereed Proceedings in International Conferences, Participation in  Technical Design Report Books and Experimental Proposals,  other Technical Report Series, Annual Reports and Presentations, participation in many International Conferences and Workshops.

      Books

    1. [1]  CMS TECHNICAL DESIGN REPORT FOR THE MUON ENDCAP GEM UPGRADE 
      This report describes both the technical design and the expected performance of the Phase-II upgrade, using Gas Electron Multiplier (GEM) detectors, of the first endcap station of the CMS muon system.
      CERN-LHCC-2015-012 ; CMS-TDR-013. - 2015. (Technical Design Report CMS ; 13) 

       

      [2]  CMS Technical Design Report for the Level-1 Trigger Upgrade 

      This report describes the technical design and outlines the expected performance of the Phase 1 Upgrade of the CMS Level-1 Trigger.
      CERN-LHCC-2013-011 ; CMS-TDR-12. - 2013. - 195 p. (Technical Design Report CMS ; 12) 

       

      [3]  CMS Technical Design Report for the Pixel Detector Upgrade 
      The original design goal of the LHC was to operate at       1×1034 cm−2s−1 with 25 ns bunch spacing, where approximately 25 simultaneous inelastic collisions per crossing (“pile-up”) occur.
      CERN-LHCC-2012-016 ; CMS-TDR-11. - 2012. - 239 p. (Technical Design Report CMS ; 11) 

       

      [4]  CMS Technical Design Report for the Phase 1 Upgrade of the Hadron Calorimeter 
      This report describes the technical design and outlines the expected performance of the Phase 1 Upgrade of the CMS Hadron Calorimeters.
      CERN-LHCC-2012-015 ; CMS-TDR-10. - 2012. (Technical Design Report CMS ; 10) 

       

      [5]  CMS TriDAS project : Technical Design Report, Volume 1: The Trigger Systems 
      CERN-LHCC-2000-038 ; CMS-TDR-6-1. - 599 p. (Technical Design Report CMS ; 6.1)
